;s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";}}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:1047:"Hi Martin,\n\nThe Union plan was a result of a years worth of work which is the plan for how the organization will develop between 2010 and 2015, which was approved by trustee board, and endorsed by council.\n\nWe allocate funds to a wide range of places, and the innovations fund is a brand new scheme approved by the trustees as a way to inject some funding into creative projects furthering the Union Plan. Rather than restricting funds this is in fact opening up a brand new opportunity that did not exist before.\n\nAs for scrutiny, decisions will be made by a panel of trustees and fed back to the full board. Further approvals will be sought in line with the financial schedules. So in the case of expenditure above £20,000 there would need to be an approval of council.\n\nIn the last two years these processes have become far more affective, and I&#039;m currently working with our Finance department to provide council with a better understanding of how the money is allocated in the Union.\n\nI hope you&#039;re getting on well since graduating.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:4:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";}}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:3:"Sam";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:4:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";}}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:1087:"<p>Hi Martin,</p>\n<p>The Union plan was a result of a years worth of work which is the plan for how the organization will develop between 2010 and 2015, which was approved by trustee board, and endorsed by council.</p>\n<p>We allocate funds to a wide range of places, and the innovations fund is a brand new scheme approved by the trustees as a way to inject some funding into creative projects furthering the Union Plan. Rather than restricting funds this is in fact opening up a brand new opportunity that did not exist before.</p>\n<p>As for scrutiny, decisions will be made by a panel of trustees and fed back to the full board. Further approvals will be sought in line with the financial schedules. So in the case of expenditure above £20,000 there would need to be an approval of council.</p>\n<p>In the last two years these processes have become far more affective, and I&#8217;m currently working with our Finance department to provide council with a better understanding of how the money is allocated in the Union.</p>\n<p>I hope you&#8217;re getting on well since graduating.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:4:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";}}}}}}i:4;a:7:{s:4:"data";s:23:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n	";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:4:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";}s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data"