ules/content/";s:3:"wfw";s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";s:2:"dc";s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";s:4:"atom";s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";s:2:"sy";s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";s:5:"slash";s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";}}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:1460:"<p>This Tuesday, at the first Media Committee of the year, we shall be electing a new position to SUSU Media &#8211; A News Coordinator. <img class="alignright  wp-image-5134" style="border: 0px" src="http://blogs.susu.org/sabbs/files/2012/09/SUSU-Media-1D1-534x540.jpg" alt="... Made on Microsoft paint" width="299" height="302" /></p>\n<p>It will be a new joint position between all the Media Departments to bring news at Southampton together. <a title="... check it out. " href="http://minutes.susu.org/files/mdacom_media_committee_-_news_co-ordinator_election.pdf" target="_blank">Here is what the role entails</a>. Any student can run for the position, with the members of media committee voting, so if you&#8217;re interested, all you have to do is turn up to <strong>Meeting Room 2 at 3pm this coming Tuesday. </strong></p>\n<p>THAT&#8217;s what makes news beautiful</p>\n<p>Nah nah nah na na&#8230;</p>\n<p>In other news, <a title="Check out the Agenda here... " href="http://minutes.susu.org/files/mdacom_agenda_2-10-2012.pdf" target="_blank">at Media Committee on Tuesday</a>, the Media Departments will approve their <a title="Here''s what we have proposed so far...  " href="http://minutes.susu.org/files/mdacom_media_committee_-_joint_goals_proposal.pdf" target="_blank">joint goals for the year </a>AND there will be a debate between the Wessex Scene and The Edge over who should cover Performing Arts content.</p>\n<p>Davey G</p>\n<p>VP Comms</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"xmlns";a:6:{s:7:"content";s:40:"http://purl.org/rs